          "text": "If you were selected, you have earned Stacc's recognition as one of the 100 best SEO influencers on Instagram for 2026.\n\nDisplay your award. Email hello@thestacc.com with the subject line \"Best SEO Instagram Influencers Badge\" and we will send you a badge image and embed code to display on your site or bio. And link back to this page.\n\n\nThese creators have earned recognition as the most authoritative SEO voices on Instagram. They eat, sleep, and breathe search engine optimization. Their feeds are filled with ranking strategies, algorithm updates, and data-backed SEO advice.\nThis is the group to follow if you want to learn SEO from people who do it for a living. These creators have built careers around helping sites rank higher in Google. Many of them have influenced how the entire industry thinks about search.\nNeil Patel ,  @neilpatel \u00b7 650K Followers\nNo pure SEO expert on Instagram commands a larger or more engaged following than Neil Patel. He covers SEO, digital marketing, and analytics across every platform. His 60-second Reels and carousel posts break down complex topics like keyword research and content optimization for business owners who do not have time for 3,000-word blog posts.\nNeil co-founded Crazy Egg, Hello Bar, and KISSmetrics. He runs NP Digital, a global marketing agency. His authority in the SEO space spans over 15 years of publishing data-driven content.\n\nWebsite: neilpatel.com\nYouTube: 1.5M subscribers\nX/Twitter: @neilpatel\nLinkedIn: Neil Patel\nBest for: All-around SEO education and quick tactical tips\n\nRand Fishkin ,  @randderuiter \u00b7 18K Followers\nFew names in SEO history carry more trust and credibility than Rand Fishkin, co-founder of Moz and now SparkToro. His Whiteboard Friday videos at Moz defined how a generation of marketers learned search optimization.\nRand now focuses on audience research and the shift toward zero-click searches. His Instagram is not his primary platform, but his influence is undeniable. He covers the future of SEO and how search behavior is changing.\n\nWebsite: sparktoro.com\nYouTube: SparkToro channel\nX/Twitter: @randfish (450K+ followers)\nLinkedIn: Rand Fishkin\nBest for: Strategic, big-picture SEO thinking and audience research\n\nAleyda Solis ,  @aleyda \u00b7 20K Followers\nConsistently named one of the most influential SEO experts in the world, Aleyda Solis stands as the definitive authority on international SEO. She runs the SEOFOMO newsletter with 30K+ subscribers and consults through her agency Orainti.\nHer Instagram covers technical SEO, international site architecture, and algorithm updates. A recommendation from Aleyda carries enormous weight among SEO professionals. She is a regular keynote speaker at Brighton SEO, MozCon, and SMX.\n\nWebsite: aleydasolis.com\nYouTube: Crawling Mondays series\nX/Twitter: @aleyda (160K+ followers)\nLinkedIn: Aleyda Solis\nBest for: International SEO, technical strategy, and multilingual site architecture\n\nLily Ray ,  @lilyraynyc \u00b7 15K Followers\nWhen it comes to decoding Google algorithm updates and E-E-A-T, no voice on Instagram is more trusted than Lily Ray. She is the VP of SEO Strategy at Amsive Digital. She speaks at major SEO conferences worldwide and her algorithm analysis threads on X regularly go viral.\nHer content breaks down how Google evaluates content quality. She covers E-E-A-T guidelines, helpful content updates, and spam updates. Business owners who need to understand why their rankings changed should follow Lily first.\n\nWebsite: lilyray.nyc\nYouTube: Conference talks and webinars\nX/Twitter: @lilyraynyc (109K+ followers)\nLinkedIn: Lily Ray\nBest for: Algorithm updates, E-E-A-T analysis, and content quality standards\n\nKevin Indig ,  @kevinindig \u00b7 12K Followers\nAmong SEO professionals who bridge the worlds of organic search and product-led growth, Kevin Indig has no peer on Instagram. He writes the Growth Memo newsletter, one of the most popular SEO newsletters, and held SEO leadership roles at Shopify and G2.\nKevin brings a data-heavy approach to SEO education. His Instagram carousels break down traffic trends, algorithm patterns, and growth frameworks. He is one of the few SEO influencers who speaks fluently about both organic search and product-led growth.\n\nWebsite: kevinindig.com\nYouTube: Growth Memo clips\nX/Twitter: @Kevin_Indig\nLinkedIn: Kevin Indig\nBest for: Growth SEO strategy for SaaS companies and marketplaces\n\nEli Schwartz ,  @elischwartz \u00b7 10K Followers\nEli Schwartz transformed how the industry thinks about SEO. And his recognition here reflects that lasting impact. He is a product-led SEO consultant and author of Product-Led SEO. He managed SEO programs at SurveyMonkey and Zendesk. His approach treats SEO as a product function rather than a marketing channel.\nHis Instagram content covers programmatic SEO, site architecture for scale, and how to align SEO with product teams. He challenges the traditional agency approach to SEO. Business owners running SaaS products benefit most from his perspective.\n\nWebsite: elischwartz.co\nYouTube: Conference presentations\nX/Twitter: @5le\nLinkedIn: Eli Schwartz\nBest for: Product-led SEO for SaaS and marketplace businesses\n\nMarie Haynes ,  @mariehaynes \u00b7 8K Followers\nFor Google algorithm recovery, there is no more trusted specialist on Instagram than Marie Haynes. She runs Marie Haynes Consulting and has helped hundreds of sites recover from manual actions and algorithmic penalties. Her newsletter breaks down every core update in detail with real examples.\nShe is one of the few SEO consultants who tracks quality rater guidelines closely. Her understanding of how Google evaluates trustworthiness is unmatched. Follow her if your site has been hit by a Google update.\n\nWebsite: mariehaynes.com\nYouTube: Algorithm update breakdowns\nX/Twitter: @Marie_Haynes\nLinkedIn: Marie Haynes\nBest for: Google penalty recovery, algorithm analysis, 