fisher \u00b7 6K Followers\nWhen complex Google Business Profile problems stump other consultants, industry professionals turn to Ben Fisher. A level of trust that earns him this recognition. He is a Google Business Profile Diamond Product Expert and co-founded Steady Demand, a local search marketing company.\nHis expertise is deep and narrow. He focuses almost exclusively on Google Business Profiles. When you have a suspended listing, a duplicate issue, or a verification problem, Ben is the person people tag on social media for help.\n\nWebsite: steadydemand.com\nX/Twitter: @BenFisher\nLinkedIn: Ben Fisher\nBest for: Google Business Profile troubleshooting, GBP suspensions, and local visibility\n\nCarolyn Lyden ,  @carolynlyden \u00b7 5K Followers\nCarolyn Lyden brings a structured, process-driven approach to local search that sets her apart from every other specialist on Instagram. She runs Search Hermit consulting and is a regular speaker at local SEO conferences.\nHer content covers local link building, review management, and small business SEO strategy. She also focuses on making SEO accessible to business owners who do not have marketing backgrounds. Her teaching style is clear and jargon-free.\n\nWebsite: searchhermit.com\nX/Twitter: @CarolynLyden\nLinkedIn: Carolyn Lyden\nBest for: Local search strategy, small business SEO, and accessible education\n\n\nThese creators have earned recognition as the most authoritative link building and off-page SEO voices on Instagram. Link building remains one of the hardest parts of SEO. Google uses backlinks as a core ranking signal.\nFollow them for link building strategies that work in 2026. The methods range from white hat digital PR to aggressive outreach campaigns. Every approach has a time and place.\nBrian Dean ,  @briandean \u00b7 35K Followers\nBrian Dean coined the Skyscraper Technique and in doing so shaped how an entire generation of SEO professionals builds links. A contribution that defines his place on this list. He founded Backlinko before selling it to Semrush.\nBrian's content is methodical and step-by-step. Every strategy includes screenshots, templates, and real examples. His YouTube channel has over 500K subscribers. Even after selling Backlinko, his educational content remains some of the best in the SEO industry.\n\nWebsite: backlinko.com\nYouTube: Backlinko (500K+ subscribers)\nX/Twitter: @BrianEDean\nLinkedIn: Brian Dean\nBest for: Link building frameworks, the Skyscraper Technique, and content-driven SEO\n\nRobbie Richards ,  @robbierichardscom \u00b7 12K Followers\nRobbie Richards produces some of the most rigorously detailed SEO tutorials and tool roundups available on any platform. A standard of quality that earns him this recognition. His website features guides often exceeding 5,000 words with screenshots for every step. He covers keyword research and link building in extreme detail.\nHis audience actively searches for SEO tools and strategies. Robbie tests every tool he recommends and provides honest comparisons. His link building tutorials break down outreach templates, prospecting methods, and follow-up sequences.\n\nWebsite: robbierichards.com\nX/Twitter: @RobbieRichMktg\nLinkedIn: Robbie Richards\nBest for: In-depth link building tutorials, SEO tool reviews, and growth marketing\n\nKasra Dash ,  @kasradash \u00b7 8K Followers\nKasra Dash has landed links from Forbes, BBC, The Guardian, and hundreds of other tier-1 publications. A campaign record that places him among the elite digital PR practitioners on Instagram. He runs Kaizen, a digital PR agency specialising in creative link building campaigns.\nHis approach combines data journalism with creative storytelling. He creates newsworthy assets that journalists want to cover. His Instagram shares campaign results and the creative process behind successful digital PR.\n\nWebsite: kaizensite.com\nX/Twitter: @KasraDash\nLinkedIn: Kasra Dash\nBest for: Digital PR link building, creative campaigns, and media outreach\n\nCharles Floate ,  @charlesfloate \u00b7 10K Followers\nCharles Floate offers something rare on Instagram: complete transparency about the full spectrum of link building. And that intellectual honesty earns him a place on this list. He has been in SEO since his teens, and his content gives a full-spectrum view of off-page SEO that most influencers avoid discussing.\nHe covers PBNs, guest posting, niche edits, and everything in between. His transparency about different approaches helps practitioners understand the full risk-reward spectrum of link building. His courses on off-page SEO are among the most detailed available.\n\nWebsite: charlesfloate.co.uk\nYouTube: Link building tutorials\nX/Twitter: @CharlesFloate\nLinkedIn: Charles Floate\nBest for: Advanced link building, full-spectrum off-page SEO, and risk assessment\n\nJames Dooley ,  @jamesdooley \u00b7 15K Followers\nJames Dooley has built and monetised one of the most impressive SEO asset portfolios in the UK. A track record that earns him recognition as one of the leading voices in SEO investing. He is a serial SEO investor and link builder who owns multiple digital businesses and ranks sites in competitive niches.\nJames shares insights about the business side of SEO. His content covers site acquisitions, portfolio management, and scaling SEO operations. He provides a perspective on SEO as an investment vehicle rather than just a marketing channel.\n\nWebsite: jamesdooley.com\nX/Twitter: @JamesDooley_\nLinkedIn: James Dooley\nBest for: SEO investing, portfolio building, and large-scale link acquisition\n\n\n3,500+ blogs published. 92% average SEO score. See what Stacc can do for your site.\nStart for $1 \u2192\n\n\nThese creators have earned recognition as the most authoritative technical SEO voices on Instagram. Technical SEO covers crawlability, indexation, site speed, structured data, JavaScript rendering, and everything under the hood.\nIf you manage a large website or work with developers, this category is essential. Technical SEO problems can prevent even the best content from ranking. These experts help you find and fix those problems.\nMark Williams-Cook ,  @markwilliamscook \u00b7 10K Followers\nMark Williams-Cook goes deeper on technical SEO than virtually any other Instagram creator. And his selection here recognises that rare depth. He hosts the Search with Candour podcast and newsletter. He built AlsoAsked, a tool for mapping People Also Ask data.\nHis technical depth sets him apart from most Instagram creators. He covers topics like log file analysis, crawl budget optimization, and rendering issues that other influencers skip entirely. His audience values honest, transparent analysis over hype.\n\nWebsite: searchcandour.com\nYouTube: Search with Candour\nX/Twitter: @MarkWilliamsCook\nLinkedIn: Mark Williams-Cook\nBest for: Technical SEO analysis, log file auditing, and data-driven search marketing\n\nAreej AbuAli ,  @areej.abu3li \u00b7 8K Followers\nAreej AbuAli built the Women in Tech SEO community from the ground up. A contribution to the SEO profession that goes far beyond follower counts. She founded this community, one of the most engaged SEO communities on the internet, which runs conferences, mentorship programs, and networking events.\nShe covers technical SEO, site migrations, and structured data. Her community includes thousands of SEO professionals who recommend tools to their clients. A mention within Women in Tech SEO reaches an outsized audience of practitioners.\n\nWebsite: womenintech.seo\nX/Twitter: @AreejAbuAli (25K+ followers)\nLinkedIn: Areej AbuAli\nBest for: Technical SEO expertise, community-driven learning, and site migrations\n\nMike King ,  @ipullrank \u00b7 12K Followers\nMike King's MozCon presentations are considered among the best in SEO conference history. A standard of excellence that earns him this recognition as one of Instagram's most authoritative technical SEO voices. He is the founder of iPullRank, a