ngagement, and deeper expertise.\nThe creators in this section are worth following early. Many of them will grow into major SEO voices over the next 1 to 2 years. Getting in early means you build relationships before their audiences scale.\nChase Reiner ,  @chasereiner \u00b7 18K Followers\nChase Reiner has built a YouTube following of 300K+ by doing something most SEO creators refuse to do: showing beginners exactly what they can accomplish with free tools today. That practical accessibility earns him recognition here. He focuses on SEO tools and automation workflows.\nHe posts tool reviews, ranking experiments, and traffic generation tactics. His approach is pragmatic. He focuses on what beginners can do today with free tools rather than what they could do with expensive software.\n\nWebsite: chasereiner.com\nYouTube: 300K+ subscribers\nX/Twitter: @ChaseReiner\nLinkedIn: Chase Reiner\nBest for: Free SEO tools, automation tactics, and beginner-friendly strategies\n\nJulian Goldie ,  @juliangoldie \u00b7 15K Followers\nJulian Goldie publishes link building case studies with real traffic screenshots and revenue figures. A commitment to transparency that makes him one of the most trusted rising voices in SEO on Instagram. He teaches SEO link building and content scaling with a focus on practical, results-driven SEO.\nHis content covers outreach templates, content production workflows, and traffic growth experiments. He is transparent about what works and what fails.\n\nWebsite: juliangoldie.com\nYouTube: 100K+ subscribers\nX/Twitter: @JulianGoldie\nLinkedIn: Julian Goldie\nBest for: Link building case studies, content scaling, and ranking experiments\n\nBrodie Clark ,  @brodieseo \u00b7 10K Followers\nBrodie Clark notices Google SERP changes before anyone else in the industry. And that obsessive tracking of how search results evolve earns him recognition as one of the most distinctive rising voices on Instagram. His newsletter documents every visual change Google make