 marketing, SEO content strategy, and tool reviews\n\nJohn Bonini ,  @johnbonini \u00b7 12K Followers\nJohn Bonini is one of the sharpest B2B content thinkers on any platform. And his willingness to challenge vanity metrics and demand revenue-focused content strategy earns him recognition here. He runs Some Good Content and writes about content marketing and B2B marketing. His LinkedIn following exceeds 30K.\nHis content focuses on creating content that drives real business outcomes, not just traffic. His audience is B2B marketers who need content that generates pipeline.\n\nWebsite: somegoodcontent.com\nX/Twitter: @bonini84\nLinkedIn: John Bonini\nBest for: B2B content marketing strategy and revenue-focused content\n\nCarl Broadbent ,  @carlbroadbent \u00b7 8K Followers\nCarl Broadbent documents his niche website journey with income reports that include exact revenue figures from display ads and affiliate programs. A rare level of honest transparency that earns him recognition as one of the most trusted rising voices in niche SEO. He shares monthly income reports and SEO experiments on YouTube and Instagram.\nHe covers keyword research, content production, monetization strategies, and traffic growth. His honest documentation of both wins and losses builds real trust.\n\nWebsite: carlbroadbent.com\nYouTube: 80K+ subscribers\nX/Twitter: @CarlBroadbent\nLinkedIn: Carl Broadbent\nBest for: Niche website building, income reports, and SEO experiments\n\nShaun Marrs ,  @shaunmarrs \u00b7 7K Followers\nShaun Marrs makes SEO genuinely accessible to small business owners who are doing their own optimization without any agency support. And that clear, jargon-free approach earns him recognition here. He creates SEO content focused on simple, actionable steps.\nHe covers on-page optimization, local SEO basics, and content creation for small business blogs. He avoids jargon and explains every concept from scratch. His teaching style is patient and practical.\n\nWebsite: shaunmarrs.com\nYouTube: SEO tutorials\nX/Twitter: @ShaunMarrs\nBest for: Simple SEO for small business owners and DIY optimization\n\nSam Oh ,  @samsgoh \u00b7 15K Followers\nSam Oh is the face of the Ahrefs YouTube channel and has introduced more people to practical SEO education through that platform than almost any other creator on this list. A reach that earns him recognition here. His teaching style is clear, patient, and data-backed, and his recommendations carry weight because they come from the team behind Ahrefs.\nHis Instagram distills long YouTube tutorials into visual formats. For more channels like his, see our guide to the best SEO YouTube channels.\n\nWebsite: ahrefs.com\nYouTube: Ahrefs (500K+ subscribers)\nX/Twitter: @samsgoh\nLinkedIn: Sam Oh\nBest for: Practical SEO tutorials backed by Ahrefs data\n\nSuganthan Mohanadasan ,  @suganthanm \u00b7 6K Followers\nSuganthan Mohanadasan tackles JavaScript SEO and enterprise rendering pipelines on Instagram. Topics that most creators on this entire list avoid entirely. And that advanced technical focus earns him recognition here. He is a technical SEO consultant specialising in enterprise and JavaScript SEO.\nHe covers topics that most SEO Instagram accounts avoid entirely. His deep dives into rendering pipelines and crawl efficiency help in-house SEOs at enterprise companies. He is a regular speaker at technical SEO conferences.\n\nWebsite: suganthan.com\nX/Twitter: @Suganthanmn\nLinkedIn: Suganthan Mohanadasan\nBest for: Enterprise technical SEO, JavaScript rendering, and crawl optimization\n\nLidia Infante ,  @lidiainfante \u00b7 7K Followers\nLidia Infante is one of the strongest voices in international SEO on Instagram and her data-rich, immediately actionable posts set a standard for technical content that few rising creators match. She is a senior SEO manager who focuses on international and technical SEO and a Women in Tech SEO community leader.\nShe covers hreflang implementation, international site architecture, and technical auditing. Her posts include real examples from enterprise sites.\n\nWebsite: lidiainfante.com\nX/Twitter: @LidiaInfanteM\nLinkedIn: Lidia Infante\nBest for: International SEO, hreflang, and technical site auditing\n\nHimani Kankaria ,  @himanijk \u00b7 8K Followers\nHimani Kankaria speaks at SEO conferences across Asia, Europe, and North America and brings a genuinely global perspective to B2B content SEO that few Instagram creators can offer. And that breadth of insight earns her recognition here. She runs Missive Digital, a content marketing and SEO agency.\nHer content covers content strategy, on-page optimization, and B2B keyword research. Her agency experience means she teaches strategies that work for real clients, not just theory.\n\nWebsite: missivedigital.com\nX/Twitter: @HimaniKankaria\nLinkedIn: Himani Kankaria\nBest for: B2B content SEO, international speaking, and content strategy\n\nMaria Amelie White ,  @mariawhiteseo \u00b7 5K Followers\nMaria White produces SaaS content SEO frameworks of a quality that far exceeds what her current follower count suggests. And recognising her now, before her audience grows, is the point of this category. She shares frameworks for turning keyword research into content strategies.\nShe covers content briefs, topic clustering, and content calendars specifically for SaaS marketing teams. She is one to follow before her audience grows.\n\nWebsite: mariawhiteseo.com\nX/Twitter: @MariaWhiteSEO\nLinkedIn: Maria Amelie White\nBest for: SaaS content strategy, topic clustering, and keyword mapping\n\n\nThese accounts have earned recognition as the most consistently valuable daily SEO education accounts on Instagram. Many are run by teams or anonymous creators rather than personal brands. They post daily tips, infographics, and cheat sheets that are easy to save and share.\n@marketingharry \u00b7 85K Followers\nOne of the largest SEO education accounts on Instagram. Posts daily digital marketing tips covering SEO basics, content strategy, and online business growth. Carousel posts break down complex concepts into swipeable steps.\n\nBest for: Digital marketing fundamentals and SEO basics for beginners\n\n@digitalmarketingtips_ \u00b7 45K Followers\nCovers digital marketing education across SEO, PPC, and social media. Posts quick-reference carousels and Reels with actionable tips. Good for marketers who want broad marketing knowledge alongside SEO.\n\nBest for: Cross-channel digital marketing tips and quick reference guides\n\n@webdevtips_ \u00b7 40K Followers\nCombines web development tips with SEO for developers. Posts cover WordPress optimization, site speed, and technical SEO from a developer perspective. Useful for web developers learning to code for search performance.\n\nBest for: Web development meets SEO, WordPress tips, and site speed optimization\n\n@thedigitalmarketer_ \u00b7 40K Followers\nPosts daily SEO, PPC, and social media tips in carousel format. Covers keyword research, on-page optimization, and analytics. Consistently publishes actionable content for digital marketing practitioners.\n\nBest for: Daily digital marketing and SEO tips in visual format\n\n@seotips.daily \u00b7 35K Followers\nPublishes daily SEO tips and tool recommendations for beginners. Carousel posts cover keyword research, on-page SEO, and free tools. One of the most consistent daily SEO education accounts on the platform.\n\nBest for: Daily SEO tips and beginner-friendly tool recommendations\n\n@theseoexpert \u00b7 28K Followers\nFocuses on SEO tutorials, ranking strategies, and on-page optimization. Posts step-by-step processes for improving search rankings. The content targets intermediate SEO practitioners looking to level up.\n\nBest for: SEO tutorials and ranking strategy walkthroughs\n\n@contentmarketingqueen \u00b7 28K Followers\nCovers content marketing strategy and blogging for business growth. Posts about editorial calendars, content planning, and SEO-driven content creation. Good for content marketers building organic traffic.\n\nBest for: Content marketing strategy and SEO-driven blogging advice\n\n@socialmediasandra \u00b7 30K Followers\nSmall business social media and marketing education. Posts cover social media strategy alongside SEO basics for local businesses. Practical advice for business owners managing their own marketing.\n\nBest for: Small business social media marketing and local SEO basics\n\n@seo.cheatsheet \u00b7 25K Followers\nPublishes SEO cheat sheets, quick tips, and tool recommendations in save-worthy formats. Posts are designed to be bookmarked and referenced later. Great for building an SEO reference library in your saved posts.\n\nBest for: Save-worthy SEO cheat sheets and quick reference guides\n\n@marketingbrewed \u00b7 25K Followers\nCovers marketing news, tool reviews, and industry updates. Posts break down marketing trends and new SEO tools. Good for staying current with the marketing technology landscape.\n\nBest for: Marketing news, tool reviews, and industry trend updates\n\n@marketingmadeeasyco \u00b7 25K Followers\nSmall business marketing education with a DIY approach. Posts cover SEO, email marketing, and social media for business owners who handle their own marketing. Practical and jargon-free.\n\nBest for: DIY marketing education for small business owners\n\n@seowithsidharth \u00b7 25K Followers\nSEO tutorials covering technical SEO and beginner guides. Posts walk through audit processes, keyword research, and on-page optimization step by step. Good for learning structured SEO processes.\n\nBest for: Step-by-step SEO tutorials and technical SEO for beginners\n\n@seo_mastery \u00b7 22K Followers\nSEO education and tool reviews with a focus on ranking strategies. Posts cover both free and paid SEO tools. Content targets intermediate practitioners who want to improve their toolkit.\n\nBest for: SEO tool reviews and intermediate ranking strategies\n\n@bizgrowthcoach \u00b7 22K Followers\nBusiness growth coaching that integrates marketing tactics including SEO. Posts cover lead generation, marketing funnels, and online business growth. Good for business owners looking for holistic growth advice.\n\nBest for: Business growth coaching and marketing-driven lead generation\n\n@contentcreatorhub \u00b7 22K Followers\nContent creation tips covering blogging, SEO, and social media. Posts help creators build an audience through search and social. Useful for bloggers and content entrepreneurs.\n\nBest for: Content creation, blogging tips, and audience building through SEO\n\n@seoinfographics \u00b7 20K Followers\nPublishes visual SEO education through infographics and data visualizations. Posts cover ranking factors, algorithm updates, and SEO statistics in easy-to-digest visual formats.\n\nBest for: Visual SEO education and infographic-style learning\n\n@seorebelution \u00b7 20K Followers\nSEO strategies, algorithm updates, and tool reviews. Posts cover both technical and content SEO with a focus on practical implementation. Good for practitioners who want actionable strategies.\n\nBest for: SEO strategies, algorithm update summaries, and tool reviews\n\n@thedigitalcoach_ \u00b7 20K Followers\nDigital marketing coaching with a focus on online business growth. Posts cover SEO, social media, and content marketing for entrepreneurs. Practical coaching-style content.\n\nBest for: Digital marketing coaching for entrepreneurs and small businesses\n\n@rankingtactics \u00b7 18K Followers\nSEO tips, content marketing, and keyword research in carousel format. Posts focus on ranking tactics that can be implemented immediately. Good for quick wins and tactical SEO advice.\n\nBest for: Quick SEO ranking tactics and keyword research tips\n\n@smallbizmarketingpro \u00b7 18K Followers\nMarketing tips specifically for small business owners. Posts cover local SEO, social media, and email marketing. Practical content for businesses with limited marketing budgets.\n\nBest for: Small b